There is no reason to think anyone is being a hypocrite here. If this research has taught us anything it teaches us that changing what we believe and changes in our perspective are constant. The things we pretend we know are constantly challenged by the things we learn from the contacts we make. The more experience in ITC we have (positive or negative) the more it reinforces the acceptance of no fear.

Now with that being said, if Bruce and Steve want to take this conversation to the negative and make it an argument then do it in private email. It is not anyone else&#39;s business if you have a &quot;bone to pick&quot; with each other.

Regards,

Frank R.

